latestIgtvVideos.title: The Truth About Acne Positivity (+Skincare Q&A)
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Some ideas seem positive on the surface, until you dig a little deeper. 

What is acne positivity?

Accepting, owning, and loving your “flaws” and all of you as is. 🥰

What it’s not:

You complaining about your skin every day.🥺

How it’s gotten twisted:

Nowadays, the acne positivity movement has gone from embracing flaws to normalising acne.🤭

Here, world, LOOK AT MY ACNE!!! LOVE ME WITH MY ACNE!!! This is what real skin looks like!!! 😳

Which is a bit whack…

That’s like normalising blisters, broken bones, yeast infections, or insert any other thing that we can generally prevent. 🙈

Acne is common, but it is only normal when we mistreat our skin — generally with terrible skincare and unhealthy habits.

So just because everyone is using this stuff and creating acne, doesn’t mean you need to. 🤓

Just because some people have accepted acne as a way of life, doesn’t mean you should too. 

And guess what, terrible skincare is very common and very normal…With new terrible skincare companies popping up almost every day!

And you keep using it because of this VERY MARKETABLE idea that “acne is normal”…

They’re literally creating it for you with their shitty AF formulas — so this messaging is awesome because you’ll think that what you have is normal, and you won’t think of treating it by avoiding the products that are causing it (which would be bad for business).

Acne positivity started with good intentions…but it’s been hijacked by companies and turned into something damaging to us, the consumer.🙈

So next time a company tells you that “acne is normal”, perhaps you should wonder if it’s only normal when you use their products…💩

Love your skin, love your flaws. But you get to decide what is normal for you.🦄

Love & Logic,
Olena 

PS. To make sure acne isn’t your normal, learn to take next level care of your skin — visit my website for more info! 👆

If you have a pretty severe skin condition...

If you've seemingly tried a LOT to solve it...

And if your skin only got worse?!

The natural assumption is "There's something wrong with me! I'm sick inside!"

However, this assumption is a mistake.

A mistake that leads you to try more things that won't work, and to trust advice of people you'd normally run from...

‼️Making ASSumptions about your skin always leads to miscommunication with your skin.

👉Like when we ASSume we know how to take care of it when we never actually learned how...

👉Or when we ASSume that the skin condition happened overnight, and we don't even begin to consider the habits (of thinking or skincare) that led us HERE...

🤓The idiom "when you hear hooves think horses, not zebras" refers to Occam's razor: that the most likely solution is the simplest one (not because simpler explanations are always correct, but because they require FEWER ASSUMPTIONS).

I want to show you another case (my 8th ever client, in fact) where appearances can be very misleading.

You'll ASSume the absolute worst thing about this girl's health even though she's perfectly healthy.

The 3-Step Moisture Method™ is still the absolute best way to moisturize.

You’d think that moisturizing your skin was super simple.
Just slap a cream on your face and call it a day. 

So when you end up with uncomfortable, tight, rough, dehydrated skin, you’re confused. 

You glob on more moisturizer, hoping to soothe your skin, hoping for glowy results…

And it doesn’t work.

Because HOW you use each step of your skincare routine is as important as WHAT you use.

Back in 2017, I shared a way to use a moisturizer to optimize our results when for the first time in my life, I didn’t experience flakes during Canadian winter.

Since then it blew up worldwide and has helped thousands of women get clearer more comfortable skin. 

It’s three steps, without waste, without nonsense.

The 3-Step Moisture Method™:

Step 1️⃣: Add tap water so that your skin is damp, not dripping wet.
Step 2️⃣: Before the water dries, add 2-4 drops of your favorite humectant serum.
Step 3️⃣: Before this dries, add a pea-size or a pea and a half of your favorite moisturizer to seal everything in.

Allow to dry. 

If you do this in the morning, wash your hands and then follow with your favorite sunscreen.
Don’t forget to do it in the evening as well, so twice a day, regardless of your made-up “skin type”.

This way, you maximize on hydration without irritating your skin or leading to other potential problems.

The idea behind the 3-Step Moisture Method™ is to give your skin just enough hydration, use just enough product and the right product, without gooping things on. 

99.9% of the skincare transformations I share here use the 3SMM…

Have you tried it yet?

Love & Logic,
O

Acne is not a full body problem. 

You don’t gain anything from making acne about everything but the surface of your skin. 

Except maybe a drawer of useless products, a cabinet of useless supplements, and possibly losing your period over food fear. 💸🎢😭

When I say that acne is a surface problem, people think that’s too simple. 

You assume that the surface of your body is simple, when it’s complex. 

You take this complexity for granted and look beyond it. It has to be something deeper. 

But your skin faces a lot of the surface, and is responsible for protecting you from the outside world. 

That’s a huge responsibility. 

Now imagine if…

🔘You’re buying poorly-formulated products
🔘Aggressing your skin with weird experiments (like DIY skincare or food on your face)
🔘Constantly changing things up
🔘Leaning over the sink inspecting your skin one inch from the mirror
🔘Picking and popping everything you find up close

How is your skin going to look?

Can I answer? 

It will look like a before picture. 📸

But it doesn’t have to be like that!

If you want clear skin focus on:
✅learning more about this incredible organ (the Skin Queen course will teach you!)
✅putting together a skin-supportive routine that suits YOUR skin
✅being consistent and patient
✅ignoring all the ads that bombard you and distract you from sticking to what really works 

Don’t believe me? Then you gotta see my Results (plural) highlights! 📸📸📸🤌

Something that most of us miss is that your skin also faces YOU. Your choices and habits. 😚

And they can be changed! 🎉🎉🎉

You can get your clear skin back if you focus on the right things.

O

latestPosts.caption:
Everyone is 👀ing for the ROOT cause of acne...

Often blaming their hormones, their diet, or their genes...

Even coming to the incorrect conclusion that “I must be sick inside! I’m stuck with it forever!”

It feels like it’s happening TO you. Like a curse! 👻

Well, few are brave enough to consider the real root cause...

It usually starts like this...

▶️Circumstances: a pimple.

▶️Thoughts: Omg, it’s acne!!

▶️Feelings: panic, confusion, frustration!

⏭️Actions: googling “how to get rid of acne”, following damaging advice from strangers on the internet, copying people’s skincare routines, jumping to conclusions, making your life revolve around your skin.

⏭️Habits: the actions from above become habitual! You do them ALL THE TIME! They start to feel normal, and you can’t temper who you were without all this.   ⏹️Results: you tell me what they are! 👀 
If you repeat CTFAHR for long enough, what do you get?

🏴‍☠️Identity: acne-sufferer.

I’ve gone this route TWICE before I learned this lesson FYI. 😇

But all of this is AVOIDABLE‼️

Circumstances that are out of our control happen all the time, like a singular pimple. 
But a singular pimple is normal and happens to healthy, clear skin.😚

Then it heals. 
Especially if you don’t interfere.‼️  How we respond to circumstances is our RESPONSIBILITY, and our approach determines our results over time.

I find that a healthy dose of self-awareness helps us change how we think, therefore how we behave, and ultimately, the results that we see.

Does this make sense?

You can of course continue looking for phantom villains, justifying why you are where you are so you can stay there.

Or you can look within, take responsibility, change your mind, and end the cycle.🤗

If you liked this post, why not share it? 😚

Love & Logic,  
O

For context, I spent over a decade learning about skin health, got rid of my own acne, have maintained clear skin for 8 yrs, and have helped thousands of people get rid of “acne” with my FREE content and paid services. 
I share a lot of general advice and best practices in my content. And I have a full roster of clients with whom I work one-on-one, and hundreds of students going through my course. 

I spend an awful LOT of time creating content for free, even if it costs me time and money to create it. 

But people act like I owe THEM something. 

Ick! 😳 f*cking ICK!! 

Nobody came to save me when I had acne. I had to roll up my sleeves and do my homework. 

And while I was elbows-deep trying to solve this problem, MY problem, I didn’t have the time nor audacity to be like this 👆. 

Now I share vetted information that actually helps people, and some of them won’t read or watch it. 😳

They won’t click over to my website for longer content. 

They won’t lift a finger. 

And then they pretend I’m not doing enough. 😳

I can’t relate to that level of learned helplessness and entitlement. 🤢

Listen, you’re either complaining or you’re helping yourself. 

I chose to do the latter, and I block those that do the former. 

I have everyone covered with different options to get your skin where it needs to be in 3-6-12 months depending on the severity of your problem.  It is your problem. Not mine.
 If none of these are a good fit, then you can do what I did and spend a decade of your time learning instead of complaining that someone didn’t give you the answer. 
 Sorry, but a girl’s gotta have some standards. 

Love & Logic,
O

PS. The girl who claims you can heal your acne with *insert product* is selling a product, not solving a problem.

Acne narratives online be like “you’re stuck with acne FOREVER!”…  Which is a bias. That f*cks your skin.  Who would spread such a horrific story about acne?  😵‍💫People who are confused about acne.  😵‍💫People who have tried so many things to get clear skin, that they’ve concluded that nothing works.  Therefore it’s forever, right?  Wrong.  The right conclusion is that your approach (throwing spaghetti at a wall) isn’t effective.  The right conclusion is that skin health is complex and that you might need to learn more.  See?  Acne narratives are self-fulfilling prophecies.  ⚠️If you think you’ll never get clear skin, you won’t…  🧠If you think there’s more to learn in how you can support and protect your skin, then you will learn and create predictable results.  The first approach sets you up to be a victim of your skin.  The second makes you curious, gathering data before jumping to conclusions.📚  Your approach determines your results. And your results reflect your approach.🫵  Want to see my results? Visit my highlights!📸  Love & Logic, O

PPS. This is a snippet from one of my YT videos — I have a channel full of helpful skincare advice and tips. Make sure to subscribe! 😎

The beauty of skincare blindness is…

Once you SEE it, you literally can’t unsee it. 

Suddenly, you look back on your skincare struggle with a whole new perspective. 

You start to notice the products on your counter and WHO influenced them. 

You start to realize that your skin started changing when you implemented this or that skincare habit. 

Maybe, it was as simple as leaning over the sink to inspect your skin up close…

That led you to see things that you didn’t notice before…👀

Things that seemed like problems that you should get rid of…

That led you to pay closer attention to skincare content and take the ADvice of random influencers…

And as your skin got worse and worse!

You decided you must be sick INSIDE!

Since, you paid a pretty penny for these miracles in jars. They couldn’t be the problem…

Could they?

Yeah, I get it. 

It’s hard to imagine that our best intentions can lead us to create problems. 

But the part that most people learn the hard way is that skin is an important, living organ. 

And you can’t just go willi-nilly with how you care for it. It’s not intuitive. 

And yet…it’s so not a part of our culture. 

We grow up taught to brush our teeth, but not to care for our skin. 

But what happens when we don’t take good care of our teeth? Sounds obvious right. 🦷

Yet due to marketing, and SO MANY MYTHS about acne, people are more likely to blame literally anything than consider their skincare habits and how they affect their skin over time. 

The good news is: if you unknowingly interfered with your skin’s function, then you can also stop! Whew! 

And learn how to support and protect it in a way that works with its biology. ✅

Love & Logic,
O
